Plans and Products for Businesses Based Outside New England
HPI specializes in employee health benefit administration for self-funded employers with 50+ employees including benefit design and administration, medical, dental, vision and ancillary claims adjudication, health management, network access, pharmacy benefits management, reporting and analysis and dedicated customer service. 
Custom-designed Benefit Plan Administration

PPO/EPO plans incorporate employer’s preferred vendors or HPI’s best-in-class vendors
High-performance plans in partnership with Employers Health Network and Southern Scripts PBM in:

Florida
South Carolina

Consumer-driven health plans (CDHPs) include flexible HRAs, HSAs, FSAs
Value-based benefit designs include incentives that steer members toward high-quality, high-efficiency healthcare providers
Navigator Open Access Planincludes a Value Based Payment (VBP) option that significantly reduces hospital costs by setting payment caps based on Medicare-plus pricing before care is delivered
Outcome-based plans tie premium reduction incentives to targeted health measures
Specialized Markets:  Municipalities, Hospitals and Healthcare Systems, Captives
Guardian DentalGuard® plans  

 Provider Networks

Employers Health Network for employers located in Florida and South Carolina
UnitedHealthcare Options PPO or UnitedHealthcare Choice Plus
Cigna Choice Fund PPO network
Most other top national and regional provider networks

 
Pharmacy Benefit Management (PBM) focused on lowering drug trend

Most major PBMs including Caremark, Express Scripts and MedImpact
Southern Scripts PBM offers 100% pass-through pricing with custom plan design options that lower drug costs on average by 25% to reverse upward trend.

Preferred A-rated Stop-Loss Carriers
A wide selection of contract and product options enable us to best meet the unique needs of your client’s company.
 

























